obic environments (1987) Geomicrobiol. J., 5, pp. 261-293; Zeikus, J.G., Fate of lignin and related aromatic substrates in anaerobic environments (1980) Lignin Biodegradation: Microbiology, Chemistry, and Potential Applications, 1. , eds. T. K. Kirk, T. Higuchi and H. Chang. CRC Press, Inc. Boca Raton, FL","Pier, P.A.; Environmental Research Center, Tennessee Valley Authority, PO Box 1010, Muscle Shoals, AL 35662-1010, United States",,,"Elsevier Science Ltd, Oxford, United Kingdom",,,,,09608524,,BIRTE,,"English","BIORESOUR. TECHNOL.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-0031239622
